radiographic_examinations.findings: Gallbladder is distended with gallbladder wall edema, an indistinct gallbladder wall, and marked degree of inflammatory stranding in the region of the gallbladder. Suggestion of focal hyperemia of the liver surrounding the gallbladder. Trace amount of free fluid seen in a perihepatic location. No drainable fluid collection identified. Liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, and adrenal glands are unremarkable. Minimal wall thickening of the antrum of the stomach and proximal duodenum. No free intraperitoneal air or pathologic adenopathy. Visualized lung bases show minimal dependent atelectasis, and no pleural effusion.
